description:
The Sims 4 is the fourth installment in The Sims franchise. Like the previous games in the series,
The Sims 4 focuses on creating and controlling a neighborhood of virtual people, called "Sims".

1.1.description: Fixed a bug where if you connect like Player1:None@ archipelago.gg it would think you connected to a different game and reset your skills

1.2.description:
Fixed the resync command giving an error when trying to use it
Added a new option to pick a career
Changed the logic to only include the picked aspiration and career in the multiworld

1.3.description:
Fixed logic where it would think that you needed 1 more skill item than you actually do
Added a useful Skill Gain multiplier item, where if you get 1 it would boost your skill gain by 2.5x and if you get 4 it would boost it by 4x 
Added a junk Career Performance boost item where it would boost your career performance to the max

1.4.description:
Fixed the /career command
Added the ability for the client to send both the aspiration and the career to the game mod in order to display both on the simphone app

1.5.description: Fixed the writers career breaking generation

1.6.1.description:
This update will ensure compatibility with the next major version of archipelago. It also backports a fix from the 2.0.0 beta version (the unreleased beta 2 version) that *should* fix issues with the game folder being in French, for the auto detection in the client.

# This release is backwards compatible with 1.6.0 and contains no breaking changes to generation or the client.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/compare/1.6.0...1.6.1

2.0.0-beta.1.description:
This is the big one. We finally have DLC support! You can randomize packs, and currently only skill levels from the DLC packs will be shuffled. Again, thank you to @silasary for the help, this would not have been possible without you! Multiple careers are also now selectable as an option, so you can have checks for more than one career. 

I'm horrible at release notes, so... this is the release notes for the beta version. Full release will *actually* have competent release notes, I swear 🤣 

## What's Changed
* Minor bugfixes by @silasary in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/1
* Select Multiple Careers by @benny-dreamly in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/3
* WIP DLC skills by @silasary in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/2
* Merge Main (Aug 12) by @benny-dreamly in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/4
* Merge Main (Aug 16) by @benny-dreamly in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/5
* Don't make location sending O(n^2) by @silasary in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/7

## New Contributors
* @silasary made their first contribution in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/1
* @benny-dreamly made their first contribution in https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/pull/3

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Simsipelago/Archipelago/compare/1.6.0...2.0.0-beta.1

sims-1.6.0.description:
**DISCLAIMER: THIS APWORLD IS NOT BACKWARDS COMPATIBLE WITH SEEDS GENERATED ON VERSION 1.5.2 OR PRIOR!** 
It will work with the prerelease 1.6.0 beta 1 world though, and you can continue seeds generated on that version.

# BREAKING CHANGES

Many location names have been changed as a result of typos found or inconsistencies with their names in-game. Thank you to @fuegobillyb for their report on this. The full list of locations changed to fix typos/inconsistencies can be found in this issue: https://github.com/benny-dreamly/Sims4ArchipelagoMod/issues/7

# Changes

- Some location names have been changed. See above comment for more details on this change.
- Item and Location Groups have been added! Thank you to everyone who suggested this throughout the course of our first beta async in the archipelago server! 
- Universal Tracker support has also been added!
  - A tab in the Client has been added to facilitate using the tracker if installed.
  - For seeds generated from now on, a yaml is no longer required to use the tracker. However, you can still provide your yaml to the tracker if you would like. 
- Various code changes behind the scenes have made the apworld easier to work on, and it now adheres better to AP code standards.

# Fixes

- Logic issues discovered during our first beta async have been fixed! Thank you to everyone who participated in testing the apworld. Your help was very appreciated to fix these issues! 


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/benny-dreamly/Archipelago/compare/sims-1.5.2...sims-1.6.0
sims-1.6.0.title: Sims 4: 1.6.0

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/benny-dreamly/Archipelago/compare/sims-1.5.2...sims-1.6.0-beta-1
